            {
               "text": "### Prerequisites\n\nThe game on this page aims to reinforce knowledge of indigenous numerical systems and the numbers we use today. Before starting, we suggest studying the following previous pages:\n- Our sides are equal: in this first text, we show for people their body symmetry (<htcite0>).\n- Couting: we introduce the idea of counting using our body (<htcite1>).\n- Beyond fingers: exploring the limitations and the necessity of new tools to count (<htcite2>).\n- Building to Count (Soroban, 算盤): In this text, we learn how Japan (Nippon-koku or Nihon-koku, 日本国) built its abacus and how to use it to count (<htcite3>).\n- Building to Count (Suanpan, 算盤): In this text, we learn about the abacus built in China (Zhōngguó, 中国) and how to represent numbers on it (<htcite4>).",
               "source": [
